Workers assemble beams for the suspension part of the Wufengshan Yangtze River Bridge in Zhenjiang, East China's Jiangsu Province. The 6.4-kilometer bridge with a span of 1,092 meters is to be the world's first suspension bridge that allows a high-speed bullet train to pass at a speed of 250 kilometers per hour. Photo: VCG
  
